# Vue and Quasar

## UI and framework

- Use Vue 3 **Composition API** (`<script setup>`) consistent with existing components.
- Prefer **Quasar** (`q-*`) components and spacing/typography patterns from sibling files in the same area.
- Keep **user-visible copy** in i18n (`src/i18n`) — never hardcode prose strings in templates, `_data/` files, or scripts.
- For SFC translations, use template `$t('camelCaseKey.subKey')` directly; do **not** import `useI18n` only to call `t(...)`.
- All top-level i18n keys use **camelCase with a lowercase first letter** (e.g. `globalWindowButtons`, `dialogs`, `errorNotFound`). Sub-keys follow the same convention.
- To add new strings: place them in a `T_*.ts` file under the matching folder (`components/<ComponentName>/`, `dialogs/`, `pages/`, or `globalFunctionality/`), import it in `src/i18n/en-US/index.ts`, and assign it to a camelCase top-level key. Do not add hardcoded strings inline to `index.ts`. Uncategorised app-wide strings belong in `globalFunctionality/T_unsortedAppTexts.ts` under `globalFunctionality.unsortedAppTexts`.
- In TypeScript scripts and Pinia stores (outside Vue templates), import `{ i18n } from 'app/src/i18n/externalFileLoader'` and call `i18n.global.t('camelCaseKey.subKey')`.
- Storybook mocks: import specific non-markdown `T_*` modules directly — never the full `en-US/index.ts` — and provide placeholder strings for `documents.*` keys. See [fantasia-i18n skill](../skills/fantasia-i18n/SKILL.md).

## After UI changes

- Run the **quality gate** — `yarn testbatch:verify` — unless debugging one step ([testing-terminal-isolation.mdc](testing-terminal-isolation.mdc)); add or update **Playwright** component tests where the project already tests similar UI (see [fantasia-testing](../skills/fantasia-testing/SKILL.md) skill).
- For components under `src/components/**`, keep Vitest parity: each `.vue` should retain a matching `tests/<ComponentName>.vitest.test.ts` suite (presence baseline, not exhaustive coverage metric).
- When adding or editing Storybook stories for `src/components/**`, place `*.stories.ts` inside each component's `tests/` subfolder (`src/components/**/tests/*.stories.ts`) and keep Storybook support wiring in `.storybook-workspace/.storybook` aligned (Quasar, Pinia, i18n mocks). Optional `src/layouts/**/tests/*.stories.ts` and `src/pages/**/tests/*.stories.ts` are **canvas-only** (no Docs/autodocs); see [storybook-stories.mdc](storybook-stories.mdc).
- Storybook i18n note: avoid importing full locale roots (`src/i18n/index.ts`, `src/i18n/en-US/index.ts`) inside Storybook mocks/helpers because markdown document imports (`documents/*.md`) can fail Vite import analysis; import specific non-markdown `T_*` modules instead and use placeholder strings for document keys.

## `<script setup>` — documentation and size

- Add a short **JSDoc block** above each significant function (`/** ... */`), as in [GlobalWindowButtons.vue](src/components/globals/GlobalWindowButtons/GlobalWindowButtons.vue).
- Keep types strict in `<script setup lang="ts">`: avoid `any`; prefer explicit interfaces, generics, unions, `unknown`, or utility types.

### When the script section grows

1. **Structured production data** (menus, button sets, large config-shaped objects the app ships): colocate under the feature in a **`_data/`** folder (e.g. [globals/AppControlMenus/_data](src/components/globals/AppControlMenus/_data/)) and import into the SFC.
   - **Split big blobs across several TS files** inside `_data/` (one concern or surface per file — name files by what they define, e.g. `project.ts`, `tools.ts`, `buttons.ts`). A single “aggregator” file that re-exports or composes smaller pieces is fine when it keeps the SFC’s imports simple.
   - **`_data/` modules are normal TypeScript**: they may call **`i18n.global.t('...')`** (or your existing locale loader pattern), import shared helpers from **`src/scripts/`**, and attach **functions** (e.g. menu `trigger` callbacks) where the shape requires dynamic behavior. Keep user-visible strings in **`src/i18n`** via keys, not hardcoded prose, unless the project already uses a local exception for that spot.
   - **Vitest fixtures** do **not** belong in `_data/` — keep them **inside** `*.vitest.test.ts` only (see [vitest-tests.mdc](vitest-tests.mdc)). **Component-testing** props for isolated SFCs should be supplied via **`COMPONENT_PROPS`** from Playwright (inline payloads in each `*.playwright.test.ts`). **Embedded** component-mode-only data that a parent SFC must own (e.g. a menu injected only when `TEST_ENV === 'components'`) may live as a **`const` in that `.vue` file** — not in a `tests/*.ts` fixture module — see [playwright-tests.mdc](playwright-tests.mdc).
   - **Do not add dedicated tests whose only SUT is a `_data/` file**; cover production `_data` through `.vue` or other consumers.
2. **Pure, reusable helpers** (no Vue instance, no template-specific state): move to **`src/scripts/`** and follow [typescript-scripts.mdc](typescript-scripts.mdc) (JSDoc, single responsibility per file).
3. **Composable-style or feature-specific logic**: keep a dedicated module under `src/scripts/<feature>/` or next to the feature if that matches existing patterns; avoid unrelated exports in one file.
4. **Large SFC script blocks split out on request** — **Do not** move bulky functions or long procedural logic out of a `<script setup>` into separate files unless the **user explicitly requests** that extraction (agents must not do this refactor proactively). When the user **does** ask for it, place the new modules **only** under **`src/components/<bucket>/<Feature>/scripts/`** (one or more `.ts` files) and import them into the SFC — **not** beside the `.vue` at the feature root. Buckets are **`dialogs/`**, **`globals/`**, **`elements/`**, **`other/`** (see [README](../../README.md)). This folder is for component-owned script logic; it is **not** a substitute for **`_data/`** (structured production payloads) or **`src/scripts/`** (shared app-wide helpers).

